				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hi Philippe,
<br />

<br />
as far as I know, a sort of Textual Confirmation functionality is already built-in into the default phpBB3 under the name &quot;custom fields&quot;. Therefore, there is no need for Textual Confirmation for phpBB3.
<br />

<br />
However, it's possible to use an universal anti-spam script, <a href="http://bbantispam.com/atc/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Advanced Textual Confirmation</a>:
<br />
<a href="http://www.phpbb.com/community/viewtopic.php?f=70&amp;t=544007" target="_blank">http://www.phpbb.com/community/viewtopic.php?f=70&amp;t=544007</a><br />_________________<br />Oleg Parashchenko, bbAntiSpam
